# Fixing the Missing Docs Panel in Storybook

The issue is likely related to your Storybook setup. Here are several steps to troubleshoot and fix the missing docs panel:

## 1. Make sure you have the docs addon installed

```bash
npm install --save-dev @storybook/addon-docs
# or with yarn
yarn add -D @storybook/addon-docs
```

## 2. Configure the docs addon in `.storybook/main.js`

Make sure your `.storybook/main.js` file has the docs addon configured:

```javascript
module.exports = {
  stories: ['../src/**/*.stories.mdx', '../src/**/*.stories.@(js|jsx|ts|tsx)'],
  addons: [
    '@storybook/addon-links',
    '@storybook/addon-essentials', // This includes docs
    '@storybook/addon-interactions',
    // Make sure the docs addon is explicitly listed if needed
    '@storybook/addon-docs'
  ],
  framework: {
    name: '@storybook/react-webpack5',
    options: {}
  },
  docs: {
    autodocs: true // Enable automatic documentation
  }
};
```

## 3. Check your story configuration

Make sure you're viewing the docs correctly:

1. In Storybook UI, click on "Docs" tab at the top of the story panel
2. If there's no "Docs" tab, you may need to:
   - Check that your Storybook version supports the current docs implementation
   - Make sure your story is properly configured with docs parameter

## 4. Update your story format

Your current format looks good but there might be issues with how the docs are being generated. Try this updated approach:

```tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from "@storybook/react";
import { Button } from "./Button";

// Add the docs page import
import { DocsPage } from "@storybook/blocks";

const meta = {
  title: "Components/Button",
  component: Button,
  tags: ['autodocs'], // Add this line to enable automatic docs
  args: {
    children: "Button",
    variant: "primary",
    icon: null,
    iconPosition: "left",
    dataSize: "medium",
    disabled: false,
    loading: false,
  },
  parameters: {
    // Use the simpler docs configuration
    docs: {
      page: DocsPage,
    },
  },
  // Rest of your configuration...
} satisfies Meta<typeof Button>;

export default meta;
// Rest of your stories...
```

## 5. Check for Storybook version compatibility

Different Storybook versions have different docs implementations. Make sure you're using the correct approach for your version:

- Storybook 7.x uses the approach shown above
- For older versions, you might need a different configuration

## 6. Restart Storybook

After making changes:

```bash
npm run storybook
# or
yarn storybook
```

