# How to Control Storybook Sidebar Order with MDX Files

To ensure "velkommen.mdx" appears before "Komigang.mdx" in the Storybook sidebar, you have several options:

## Method 1: Use Numeric Prefixes in Title

The simplest approach is to add numeric prefixes to your Meta titles:

```jsx
// velkommen.mdx
<Meta title="Documentation/01-Velkommen" />

// Komigang.mdx
<Meta title="Documentation/02-Komigang" />
```

Storybook will sort these alphabetically, so the numbering will control the order.

## Method 2: Configure Story Sorting in .storybook/preview.js

You can explicitly define the order in your Storybook configuration:

```javascript
// .storybook/preview.js
export const parameters = {
  options: {
    storySort: {
      order: [
        'Documentation', 
        ['Velkommen', 'Komigang'], // Sub-items in the Documentation section
        'Components',
        // other sections...
      ],
    },
  },
};
```

This gives you precise control over the order of all your stories.

## Method 3: Use the `sortStories` Parameter

For more complex sorting logic:

```javascript
// .storybook/preview.js
export const parameters = {
  options: {
    storySort: (a, b) => {
      // Custom sorting logic
      const order = {
        'Documentation/Velkommen': 1,
        'Documentation/Komigang': 2,
        // Add other stories as needed
      };

      const aValue = order[a[1].title] || 999;
      const bValue = order[b[1].title] || 999;
      return aValue - bValue;
    },
  },
};
```

## Method 4: File Naming Convention (Less Reliable)

If Storybook is scanning your files in alphabetical order, you could name the files to control the order:

```
01-velkommen.mdx
02-Komigang.mdx
```

However, this is less reliable than the other methods as it depends on how Storybook scans your files.

## Best Practice

The most reliable approach is a combination of Method 1 and Method 2:

1. Use numeric prefixes in your Meta titles for basic ordering
2. Configure explicit sort order in `.storybook/preview.js` for precise control

This will ensure "velkommen.mdx" consistently appears before "Komigang.mdx" in the Storybook sidebar, regardless of any other changes you make to your Storybook configuration.
