# Adding Your Logo to Storybook UI - Easiest Method

The easiest way to add your own logo to Storybook UI is by using the Storybook theming API. Here's a step-by-step guide:

## Step 1: Create a Theme File

Create a new file called `.storybook/YourTheme.js` (or `.ts` if using TypeScript):

```javascript
// .storybook/YourTheme.js
import { create } from '@storybook/theming/create';

export default create({
  base: 'light', // or 'dark'

  // Brand information
  brandTitle: 'Your Company Name',
  brandUrl: 'https://your-website.com',
  brandImage: '/your-logo.png', // Path to your logo
  brandTarget: '_self',

  // Optional: UI colors
  colorPrimary: '#4a4a4a',
  colorSecondary: '#0971f1',
});
```

## Step 2: Add Your Logo to Static Directory

Place your logo file in the Storybook static directory:

1. Create a folder `.storybook/static/` if it doesn't exist
2. Add your logo file there (e.g., `.storybook/static/your-logo.png`)

## Step 3: Apply the Theme in manager.js

Create or edit `.storybook/manager.js`:

```javascript
// .storybook/manager.js
import { addons } from '@storybook/manager-api';
import YourTheme from './YourTheme';

addons.setConfig({
  theme: YourTheme,
});
```

## Step 4: Configure Static Files (if needed)

Make sure Storybook knows about your static directory in `.storybook/main.js`:

```javascript
// .storybook/main.js
module.exports = {
  // your existing config...
  staticDirs: ['../public', './static'],
};
```

## Step 5: Restart Storybook

```bash
npm run storybook
# or
yarn storybook
```

That's it! Your logo should now appear in the top-left corner of the Storybook UI.

## Alternative Quick Option

If you just want to quickly change the logo without a full theme, you can use a simpler approach:

```javascript
// .storybook/manager.js
import { addons } from '@storybook/manager-api';

addons.setConfig({
  theme: {
    brandImage: '/your-logo.png',
    brandTitle: 'Your Company Name',
  },
});
```

This is the absolute easiest way to add your logo to Storybook UI with minimal configuration.
